        "data": {
          "comment": "# 🃏 Flashcard Generator\n\nEnter a topic; an AI writes each card as a structured front/back/category object (not a markdown blob), so downstream steps can store, query, and render them as real data — then saves the deck to SQLite and reads it back for review.\n\n**Pipeline:** Topic + card count → build prompt → generate card objects → insert into SQLite → query all\n\n**Try this:** change the topic or card count. Cards persist across runs — rerun to add more to the same deck."
        },
